# MiroFish Deep-Dive: What It Is, What's Extractable, and How It Maps to Your World

## What MiroFish Actually Is

**Repository:** [666ghj/MiroFish](https://github.com/666ghj/MiroFish) — 46k stars, 6.5k forks, #1 GitHub Trending March 2026

MiroFish is a **swarm intelligence prediction engine**. The core idea:

> Instead of asking ONE AI "what will happen?", spawn THOUSANDS of AI agents with unique personalities, drop them into a simulated social environment, and watch what *emerges* from their collective behavior.

### The 5-Step Pipeline

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["📄 Seed Data<br/>(news, report, policy)"] --> B["🕸️ Knowledge Graph<br/>(GraphRAG)"]
    B --> C["🧬 Agent Creation<br/>(1000s of personas)"]
    C --> D["🌐 Social Simulation<br/>(OASIS Engine)"]
    D --> E["📊 Prediction Report<br/>(ReportAgent)"]
    E --> F["💬 Deep Interaction<br/>(talk to any agent)"]
```

1. **GraphRAG** parses input documents into a knowledge graph (entities + relationships)
2. **Agent Factory** spawns thousands of agents, each with unique personality, memory, stance
3. **OASIS Engine** runs them in parallel simulated social platforms (Twitter/Reddit clones)
4. **ReportAgent** analyzes emergent behaviors → structured prediction report
5. **Deep Interaction** — you can interrogate any individual agent post-simulation

### Tech Stack
| Layer | Tech |
|-------|------|
| Backend | Python (57.8%), OASIS framework |
| Frontend | Vue (41.1%) |
| Knowledge | GraphRAG, Neo4j (in offline variant) |
| Memory | Zep Cloud (persistent agent memory) |
| LLMs | Any OpenAI-compatible API (default: Qwen-plus via Alibaba) |
| Infra | Docker, docker-compose |

